<paragraph id="CB78F2A7AC0821D106F3106CB3923DF7" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Other material examined.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0710CB475FB1DB20F26E458176440617" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
Only known from 
<typeStatus id="5024B1AF3574C325D322484E5267350D">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CAA2FA8553FCE31A4F04037DCA9C4E53" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="7AA2A3A822C7DE792682CE43D71AB8CB" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A54539080D900874590FD043F31B0C4B" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">The specific epithet is a noun in apposition referring to the type locality.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BDE007EC3C22CB1D2A5498E52DDD7AC3" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="747C0646AFC446F9A1129D1424D75503" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="068614CCD165EE7BABDE216FAE939A9E" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="88E20F9BF88CCAB33F1FD307A90DBF99" genus="S." lsidName="S. neneba" order="Araneida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="neneba">
<emphasis id="CAE60410089E7075F6CAD5E99A720F11" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">S. neneba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. are unknown. Genitalia of female specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="2D9CA08AFB5F3F4BC9A7D18DBA2B1F31" genus="S." lsidName="S. neneba" order="Araneida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="neneba">
<emphasis id="6556B5209540F8865F07119E6B67D40C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">S. neneba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. can be recognised by the somewhat sinuous antero-lateral edges of the epigyne plate and the transverse edges in the atrium (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CEE9D552EBA2322F1D4BC90735757B9B" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Salsa neneba sp. nov., female holotype (QM S 111920) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view. Scale bars: 5 mm (A, B); 0.1 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686614" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">15C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3CCE3ECC0BB8CB183135D370CFEE97BE" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="description">
<paragraph id="58678F39B49DEBC6C1749A84B9410CBB" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6B4772F71A9B754EAD8CB46DE8ED4678" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis id="88C63667F71B990B5CDB95462F6BA21D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7D38C1825BAA2A9BC7DE67501A53CEB5" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis id="1EF4BA6088271B2FD393BC57C08A5731" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Female</emphasis>
(based on holotype, QM S111920): Total length 10.5. Carapace 4.5 long, 3.2 wide; dark reddish brown and covered by white setae anteriorly from fovea (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="721C8542DE8E66DE459583E46F8428B7" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Salsa neneba sp. nov., female holotype (QM S 111920) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view. Scale bars: 5 mm (A, B); 0.1 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686614" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">15A</figureCitation>
). Eye diameter AME 0.23, ALE 0.18, PME 0.20, PLE 0.16; row of eyes: AME 0.68, PME 0.56, PLE 2.25. Chelicerae reddish brown, four promarginal teeth (apical and second basal largest) and three retromarginal teeth (apical smallest). Legs yellowish brown, femora slightly darker (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="756274BF1636530C10D1D2066E17A251" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Salsa neneba sp. nov., female holotype (QM S 111920) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view. Scale bars: 5 mm (A, B); 0.1 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686614" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">15A, B</figureCitation>
). Pedipalp length of segments (femur + patella + tibia + tarsus = total length): 1.2 + 0.5 + 0.8 + 1.1 = 3.6. Leg formula I&gt; II&gt; IV&gt; III; length of segments (femur + patella + tibia + metatarsus + tarsus = total length): I - 3.8 + 1.7 + 3.2 + 2.8 + 1.0 = 12.5, II - 3.5 + 1.6 + 2.6 + 2.6 + 0.9 = 11.2, III - 2.1 + 1.0 + 1.2 + 1.3 + 0.7 = 6.3, IV - 3.3 + 1.4 + 2.3 + 2.3 + 0.8 = 10.1. Labium 0.58 long, 0.77 wide, reddish brown; endites reddish brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3B4B610D7F82FB251BDCEAC56C8A7D69" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Salsa neneba sp. nov., female holotype (QM S 111920) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view. Scale bars: 5 mm (A, B); 0.1 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686614" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">15B</figureCitation>
). Sternum 2.0 long, 1.8 wide, reddish brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="289D0993805DCF22EB5AB692C4B5A8B2" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Salsa neneba sp. nov., female holotype (QM S 111920) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view. Scale bars: 5 mm (A, B); 0.1 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686614" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">15B</figureCitation>
). Abdomen 6.1 long, 5.0 wide; posterior hump distinct (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CDFE183F70FCD5A9CC083C49607D015C" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Salsa neneba sp. nov., female holotype (QM S 111920) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view. Scale bars: 5 mm (A, B); 0.1 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686614" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">15A, B</figureCitation>
); dorsum colouration poorly preserved, beige with indistinct greyish folium pattern (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D7FB5A43A7BC39BE3138FD91F7F3B0BA" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Salsa neneba sp. nov., female holotype (QM S 111920) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view. Scale bars: 5 mm (A, B); 0.1 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686614" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">15A</figureCitation>
); venter olive-brown with two spindle-shaped pale lateral bands (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="FDE7C63DD219EA58FDE81AAF5BDCD6B4" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Salsa neneba sp. nov., female holotype (QM S 111920) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view. Scale bars: 5 mm (A, B); 0.1 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686614" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">15B</figureCitation>
). Epigyne ca. as long as wide, with sinuous antero-lateral borders and transvers ridges within the atrium (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AD5F33EFB01BD84057C9F322AC7E13B7" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Salsa neneba sp. nov., female holotype (QM S 111920) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view. Scale bars: 5 mm (A, B); 0.1 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686614" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">15C</figureCitation>
); scape slightly longer than half the length of the epigyne base, slightly narrowest centrally (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6D5B3DFBE6AEAD1A74D1908FAFDA76EF" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Salsa neneba sp. nov., female holotype (QM S 111920) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view. Scale bars: 5 mm (A, B); 0.1 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686614" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">15C</figureCitation>
); epigyne not dissected to investigate posterior and internal morphology as only known from fragile holotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="990FA25DE4BDAC888D2789DFF5C94FFF" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="variation">
<paragraph id="20149A89C619CEA9BC96348D1B9C6595" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Variation.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6E991067B669098527D6EA904C291C70" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Only known from holotype.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7D8549A195C12D122B41E3520C752CCD" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="life history and habitat preferences">
<paragraph id="4FD99EEA879EABEBB1D89EAA80629E51" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Life history and habitat preferences.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CFBF193DA44928E214AD28CA9609E4D2" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="13025B3C3C07A80A0C088E8DF1AD22A3" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BEE112BFA78CFE74CEBB1A3076EC74E" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="90CA3E28C01BBDCA66C84C828B2DFBC7" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
